This week Pastor Ted Wilson continues discussion on chapter seven of The Great Controversy, entitled â€œLutherâ€™s Separation from Romeâ€ in which Luther posts the 95 Theses on the door of the castle church in Wittenberg. The news of this bold act and the 95 theses spread like wildfire across Germany and beyond, enraging all of Rome. 

Despite the threat of prison, torture, and death, Luther remained faithful and refused to recant. When a decree from Rome arrived condemning and excommunicating Luther, he burned it publicly along with other decrees and documents asserting papal power.

To learn more about Lutherâ€™s separation from Rome, and how it relates to our present experience, read The Great Controversy by Ellen White at https://greatcontroversyproject.org/.
